LEAD COOK (Milwaukie)

Compensation: $15-$16 per hour
Full Time Position
Job Location: 13121 SE McLoughlin Blvd near Park

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Job Duties include:
Oversee day-to-day culinary operations
Coordinate food and kitchenware orders
Check freshness and quality of ingredients
Assist in the development of menu items
Work with management to create a memorable experience for guests

Qualifications for this position include:
Five years cooking experience in restaurant
Two years banquet experience
Knowledge of safety and health compliance standards
Written and verbal communication skills
Food handlers certification
Must pass background check & drug test

Target Enterprise, Inc. is seeking a full-time Senior Engineer at our offices in Minneapolis, MN. The Senior Engineer will be responsible for driving industry-leading software development technologies in support of every angle of the business, and help ensure that Target operates smoothly, securely and reliably.

This position requires a Bachelor's degree or equivalent in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or a related field and 5 years related (progressive, post-baccalaureate) experience. Must also have 12 months of demonstrated ability (which may have been gained concurrently) with each of the following: (1) leading and conducting code review, design review, testing, and debugging activities at the application level; (2) writing code to build functional user interfaces by using software development practices and enterprise coding standards; (3) configuring continuous integration and deployment workflow to automate the test, build and deployment cycle; (4) developing tools and scripts to automate repetitive tasks in the development workflow; and (5) utilizing the following technologies: Java Springboot, Microsoft .Net, AngularJS, MongoDB, Kubernetes, Docker, Jenkins, Drone, Github, PostgresDB, Microsoft SQL Server, Microsoft Infopath.
